<TITLE> Barapukuria residents launch hunger strike </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dinajpur, March 10 (bdnews24.com)  Some 1,000 residents of the Barapukuria coal mine area have started a hunger strike demanding compensation and permanent rehabilitation from the government. They began their fast at midday under the banner of the Committee to Protect Life and Property. "All the houses in the area are crumbling and the crust of the soil is breaking," said Layebuddin, a resident of the area. "We are already dead. If we can get some compensation then our families can live," he said. The fast will continue until the demands are met, convener of the committee Ibrahim Khalil told bdnews24.com. Police have been posted in the area but no untoward incident was reported. bdn
